      static final String[] defaults

  • Method Details

    • getSta

      String getSta()
      Station code. This is the code name of a seismic observatory and identifies a geographic location recorded in the site table.

    • getOndate

      long getOndate()
      Turn on date. Date on which the station, or sensor indicated began operating. The columns offdate and ondate are not intended to accommodate temporary downtimes, but rather to indicate the time period for which the columns of the station (lat, lon, elev,) are valid for the given station code. Stations are often moved, but with the station code remaining unchanged.

    • getOffdate

      long getOffdate()
      Turn off date. This column is the Julian Date on which the station or sensor indicated was turned off, dismantled, or moved (see ondate)

    • getLat

      double getLat()
      Geographic latitude. Locations north of equator have positive latitudes.

      Units: degree

    • getLon

      double getLon()
      Geographic longitude. Longitudes are measured positive East of the Greenwich meridian.

      Units: degree

    • getElev

      double getElev()
      Surface elevation. This column is the elevation of the surface of the earth above the seismic station (site) relative to mean sea level

      Units: km

    • getStaname

      String getStaname()
      Station name/Description. This value is the full name of the station whose code name is in sta [for example, one record in the site table connects sta = ANMO to staname = ALBUQUERQUE, NEW MEXICO (SRO)].

    • getStatype

      String getStatype()
      Station type; character string specifies the station type. Recommended entries are single station (ss) or array (ar).

    • getRefsta

      String getRefsta()
      Reference station. This string specifies the reference station with respect to which array members are located (see deast, dnorth).

    • getDnorth

      double getDnorth()
      Distance North. This column gives the northing or relative position of array element North of the array center specified by the value of refsta (see deast).

      Units: km

    • getDeast

      double getDeast()
      Distance East. This column gives the easting or the relative position of an array element East of the location of the array center specified by the value of refsta (see dnorth).

      Units: km

    • parseSite

      static String[] parseSite(String string) throws IOException
      • If string contains a tab character, it is parsed using tab as delimiter.
      • Otherwise it is parsed with white space.
      • If parsing with white space and line contains two or more quotes, staname is assumed to be in quotes.
      • Any quotes that enclose any tokens other than those enclosing staname are ignored.
      • This parser can parse the results of database query select sta, ondate, offdate, lat, lon, elev, staname, statype, refsta, dnorth, deast.
      The string may contain fewer than 11 tokens:
      • if string contains only 4 tokens, they are assumed to be sta, lat, lon, elev
      • otherwise, as many values as possible are parsed and all others are default values.
      Parameters:
      string -
      Returns:
      11 tokens, some of which may contain default values
      Throws:
      Exception
      IOException

    • getSite

      static Site getSite(String string) throws Exception
      Parse string into a new Site object.
      • If string contains a tab character, it is parsed using tab as delimiter.
      • Otherwise it is parsed with white space.
      • If parsing with white space and line contains two or more quotes, staname is assumed to be in quotes, otherwise staname is assumed to not contain any white space.
      • Any quotes that enclose any tokens other than those enclosing staname are ignored.
      The string may contain fewer than 11 tokens:
      • if string contains only 4 tokens, they are assumed to be sta, lat, lon, elev
      • otherwise, as many values as possible are parsed and all others are default values.
      Parameters:
      string - String to be parsed
      Returns:
      a gov.sandia.gmp.util.globals.Site object
      Throws:
      Exception
